  "title": "Business Development Executive",
  "description": "<p>We are looking for a proactive and motivated <strong>Business Development Executive</strong> to support sales activities and client engagement for our Industry business unit. This role suits someone with basic technical knowledge and strong interest in business development.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><p><strong>Sales Support & Lead Generation</strong></p><p><br />    •    Identify new leads, develop prospect lists, and conduct outreach to potential clients.<br />    •    Support the preparation of quotations, proposals, pre-qualifications, and tender submissions.<br />    •    Maintain and update CRM systems, sales reports, and activity logs.</p><p><strong>Client Engagement</strong></p><p><br />    •    Build positive relationships with relevant stakeholders.<br />    •    Coordinate client meetings, presentations, and follow-ups.<br />    •    Assist with resolving client issues in coordination with operations team. </p><p><strong>Market & Competitor Research</strong></p><p><br />    •    Monitor opportunities of upcoming projects and shutdown/turnaround activities.<br />    •    Collect and report market intelligence, trends, and competitor activity.</p><p><strong>Internal Coordination</strong></p><p><br />    •    Liaise with operation team to ensure accurate proposals and timely service delivery.<br />    •    Support marketing initiatives such as digital campaigns, brochures, and events.</p><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><p><br />    •    Diploma/Degree in Engineering, Business, or related fields.<br />    •    1–3 years of experience in sales, customer service, or technical support (preferably O&G or engineering).<br />    •    Basic understanding of inspection services is an advantage.<br />    •    Strong communication skills, customer-focused attitude, and willingness to learn.<br />    •    Fresh graduates with strong interest in O&G business development are welcome.<br />    •    Ability to multitask and manage deadlines.</p>",
